postcontent:
Brand new in the box, only opened to check out how awesome it is. Retail is $2999.99 plus shipping. Asking $2500 or open to trades or OBO. Thanks for looking.


The FLIR Scout PS-32 Handheld Thermal Monocular 0009-01-00S is an incredibly portable thermal imaging monocular that will serve you well on the trail, in the home, or during a hunt. These highly compact Thermal Imaging devices weigh just twelve ounces, and they're less than seven inches long, making for a Monocular that you can easily stuff in your pack, pocket, or pouch. With the FLIR Scout PS32 Portable Thermal Camera in your pack, you can easily pick out heat signatures in any environment, even through fog, smoke, dust, and foliage. FLIR Systems has equipped the PS32 with three selectable palettes - white hot, black hot, and InstAlert (thermal signatures show up bright red on a black and white background) - to instantly tailor your view to your surroundings. Intuitive three-button operation on the FLIR Scout PS 32 Digital Zoom Thermal Monocular makes it simple to customize brightness, contrast, and polarity.

Like other thermal monoculars, the FLIR PS-32 Scout Heat Seeking Thermal Imager is useful for a number of pursuits, from detecting drafts and leaks in your house, to finding lost pets, to tracking injured game, to home defense. The FLIR Systems thermal imager is efficient, too, powered by arechargeable lithium-ion internal battery that will last for up to 5 hours without needing a charge. When you need close-range illumination for a hands-on task, the FLIR Systems Scout PS32 Heat Seeking Handheld Monocular utilizes an embedded LED task light that will give you all the non-thermal illumination you need. And for added stability, the PS32 Scout features a 1/4-20 Tripodmount. If you want to see clearly at night or in vision-impairing conditions, use the portable power of the FLIR Systems PS-32 Scout 320x240 Thermal Vision Monocular.

1968 Walther P-38. 
Non Import
It was manufactured in Ulm West Germany
It is the highly collectable “Single Line” Slide
Has the military acceptance proof marks of the eagle N, as well as the dot in a circle and the star on the takedown lever
Originally produced for the post war German Army or Police – then sold in the civilian market at German Racquet Sporting Clubs.
It is not imported, but brought here by someone who purchased it there.
Comes with the original box with matching serial number to the gun, manual, factory target, cleaning rod, an extra set of WWII grips, and three magazines. 
1962 West German Polizi leather holster
98% Bluing
Had to go to the Walther forums to research and find that the "One line slide" is very desirable to collectors.
This is made in between the P-38 and P-1 eras and is made with military parts
The value is put between $600-$700 and it will only go up in time.

Hey all. 

Had a deal on this, but they bailed out after making me drive an hour and wait two. So to try this again....


I picked up this awesome weapon in trade, but because I already have a hand cannon, I am not as in love with it as I thought. It is an awesome piece, and is a first gen Israeli import pistol. title: For Sale:  Noveske NSR AR15 Rail - 13.5"
postcontent:
Changing to a shorter barrel on my AR and this rail is now too long for me.

Barrel Nut shows some wear from torquing.

Rail shows some wear around bolt holes that connect it to the barrel nut.

Currently has 31 LaRue IndexClips Installed - These can be included for additional cost.

Currently has Deuck Defense Rapid Transition Sight Installed - This, and the matching rear sight can be included for additional cost.

From Noveske's Website:
The NSR handguard was designed with the goal of being the lightest and smallest free floating forend option to the M16 family of weapons. The width of the NSR handguard before accessories have been installed is only 1.48" The NSR handguard is available for sale as standard equipment on our rifles and upper assemblies, as well as a separate component for sale to the public. Available in 7", 9", 11", 13.5", 15" and 16.7" lengths. 

The KeyMod inter-locking rail system is a collaboration between Vltor Weapon Systems and Noveske Rifleworks. Separately, both companies were in development of their own systems, but later realizing that both systems were similar, a standardization of the KeyMod system came to be. 

The KeyMod system offers a mounting platform for a variety of (future) accessories and components. The days of the Picatinny Rail (MIL-STD-1913) are numbered. The future of the direct mountable accessory is here and now. The KeyMod self-contained components/mounting hardware index and V-block onto the platform, achieving a secured and accurate hold to the system, while separate lugs take the recoil force off the fasteners. The pass through attachment method eliminates the need for loose screws and backing plates that can easily be lost, or difficult to install. Another advantage of the KeyMod system over the 1913 system is the direct attach eliminates the need for the 1913 system as a "middle Man" thereby reducing weight and accessory off-set from the center of the handguard.

Overall, the Taurus PT-92 is an excellent pistol necessary for these modern times.
